<treatment ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615649" ID-GBIF-Taxon="180586836" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4615649" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:72141214A544FFA0CE23FBB1A0A9F919" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/72141214A544FFA0CE23FBB1A0A9F919" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[809,1443,263,1791]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
To find the appropriate name for the FR morphotype, we sought post-1758 descriptions of 
<emphasis box="[1330,1383,1095,1119]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">rufus</emphasis>
-like slugs from continental Europe. We believe the name having priority is 
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[1030,1350,1159,1183]" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Limax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[1030,1163,1159,1183]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Limax ruber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE" box="[1170,1350,1159,1183]" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref25633" refString="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE 1764. Les figures des plantes et an- imaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy medecin, dessines d'apres nature par Mr. de Garsault, graves par Mrs. Defehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet &amp; c. Niquet scrip. Vol. 5. Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 49481" title="Les figures des plantes et an- imaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy medecin, dessines d'apres nature par Mr. de Garsault, graves par Mrs. Defehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet &amp; c. Niquet scrip. Vol. 5" type="book" year="1764">Garsault, 1764</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE" box="[815,1080,1191,1215]" journalOrPublisher="Didot, Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref25711" refString="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE 1767. Description, vertus et usages de sept cents dix-neuf plantes, tant etrangeres que de nos climats; et de cent trente-quatre animaux, en sept cents trente planches, gravees en taille-douce, sur les desseins d'apres nature, de M. de Garsault, par MM. de Fehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet, &amp; c. Et rangees suivant l'ordre du livre intitule Matiere Medicale de M. Geoffroy. Ouvrage utile a toutes matieres medicales, aux artistes, aux personnes charitables, &amp; a tous ceux qui preparent eux-memes leurs medicaments. Didot, Paris." title="Description, vertus et usages de sept cents dix-neuf plantes, tant etrangeres que de nos climats; et de cent trente-quatre animaux" type="book" volumeTitle="sept cents trente planches, gravees en taille-douce, sur les desseins d'apres nature, de M. de Garsault, par MM. de Fehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet, &amp; c. Et rangees suivant l'ordre du livre intitule Matiere Medicale de M. Geoffroy. Ouvrage utile a toutes matieres medicales, aux artistes, aux personnes charitables, &amp; a tous ceux qui preparent eux-memes leurs medicaments" year="1767">GARSAULT (1767: 376)</bibRefCitation>
described as a red brown slug, larger than 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1102,1223,1247]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pomatia">
<emphasis box="[950,1102,1223,1247]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Helix pomatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. His illustration (
<bibRefCitation author="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref25633" refString="GARSAULT F. A. P. DE 1764. Les figures des plantes et an- imaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy medecin, dessines d'apres nature par Mr. de Garsault, graves par Mrs. Defehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet &amp; c. Niquet scrip. Vol. 5. Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 49481" title="Les figures des plantes et an- imaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy medecin, dessines d'apres nature par Mr. de Garsault, graves par Mrs. Defehrt, Prevost, Duflos, Martinet &amp; c. Niquet scrip. Vol. 5" type="book" year="1764">GARSAULT 1764</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 644; https://gdz.sub.uni-goettingen.de/id/ PPN496755056) is recognisably an 
<taxonomicName box="[1243,1305,1288,1311]" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Arion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1305,1288,1311]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Arion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species on account of the position of the pneumostome. Judging from other illustrations, the pale lateral band in this illustration is merely the artist’s device to indicate the round form. No locality was given, but the neighbourhood of Paris, where Garsault worked (
<bibRefCitation author="SCHULTES F. W. &amp; KLUG R. &amp; LUTZE A." box="[813,1057,1479,1503]" journalOrPublisher="F. A. P. de Garsault in 1764. Archives of Natural History" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="118 - 127" part="35" refId="ref29545" refString="WELTER- SCHULTES F. W., KLUG R., LUTZE A. 2008. Les figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, a rare work published by F. A. P. de Garsault in 1764. Archives of Natural History 35: 118 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.3366 / E 0260954108000119" title="Les figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, a rare work" type="journal article" year="2008">WELTER-SCHULTES et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) is the most reasonable assumption. This would be compatible with occurrences of 
<emphasis box="[816,834,1543,1567]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">fr</emphasis>
in that area (
<bibRefCitation author="ZEMANOVA M. A. &amp; KNOP E. &amp; HECKEL G." box="[1016,1298,1543,1567]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="5747 - 5764" part="25" refId="ref29854" refString="ZEMANOVA M. A., KNOP E., HECKEL G. 2016. Phylogeographic past and invasive presence of Arion pest slugs in Europe. Molecular Ecology 25: 5747 - 5764. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mec. 13860" title="Phylogeographic past and invasive presence of Arion pest slugs in Europe" type="journal article" year="2016">ZEMANOVA et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). However, it would be desirable to designate a neotype to remove all doubt about the correspondence of 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ruber</emphasis>
with the FR morphotype, as is our future intention. The name of the FR morphotype becomes
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
